What you need to know:

Then companies started scrambling for the tenders in the multi-billion plan as cash flowed into government coffers to deal with the novel coronavirus.Kilig Limited was awarded a Sh4 billion tender for the procurement of 450,000 kits each valued at Sh9,000, through a direct procurement, and questions were raised about the tender.Komtel Kenya Limited got four tenders: to supply 1,000 surgical face masks in packs of 50 at Sh4,500 each, earning Sh90 million and an additional 200,000 NK95 face masks at Sh700 each, totalling Sh140 million